servings: 2
source: https://www.hellofresh.com/recipes/easy-peasy-ravioli-gratin-5bbb9830ae08b503891422d2
---

Wash and dry all produce. Preheat broiler to high or oven to 500 degrees. Halve,
peel, and thinly slice half the @yellow onion{1/2} (use the other half as you
like). Strip @thyme{1/4%ounce} leaves from stems; discard stems.

Melt @butter{1%tablespoon} in a #large pan{} over medium heat (use an
ovenproof pan if you have one). Add thyme and onion. Cook until softened,
~{5-6%minutes}. Season with @salt{} and @pepper{}. Pour in @veggie stock
concentrate{1} and 1 cup water and bring to a simmer.

Add @spinach and ricotta ravioli{9%ounce} to pan. Cover and cook ~{4%minutes}.
Uncover and increase heat to high. Continue cooking, spooning stock over
ravioli, until ravioli are tender and stock has reduced, ~{5-6%minutes}. Shake
pan occasionally to keep ravioli from sticking.

Combine @panko breadcrumbs{1/4%cup}, @parmesan cheese{1/4%cup}, a drizzle of
@olive oil{a drizzle}, and a pinch of salt and pepper in a #small bowl{}.

Remove pan from heat. Carefully stir @sour cream{4%tablespoon} and
@spinach{5%ounce} into pan until thoroughly combined and spinach is wilted.
Season with salt and pepper. (TIP: Add up to ½ cup water if sauce seems very
thick.) If your pan is not ovenproof, transfer mixture to a #baking dish{} at
this point.

Sprinkle ravioli in pan (or dish) with crust mixture. Place under broiler and
broil until golden brown, ~{1-2%minutes}. Divide between plates and serve.

